{# 
    Table Body (<tbody>)
    ===========================================================================

    Defines the body content of a table.

    Variables:
    - `table_rows`: A list of rows for the table body, each row represented as a list of cells. Defaults to [["Row 1 Cell 1", "Row 1 Cell 2", "Row 1 Cell 3"], ["Row 2 Cell 1", "Row 2 Cell 2", "Row 2 Cell 3"]].

    Notes:
    - The `| e` filter is used to escape any special characters in the variables to prevent XSS attacks.
    - The <tbody> element is used to group the body content in an HTML table.

    Links:
    - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/tbody
    - https://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_tbody.asp

#}

<tbody>
    {% for row in table_rows | default([['Row 1 Cell 1', 'Row 1 Cell 2', 'Row 1 Cell 3'], ['Row 2 Cell 1', 'Row 2 Cell 2', 'Row 2 Cell 3']]) %}
        <tr>
            {% for cell in row %}
                <td>{{ cell | e }}</td>
            {% endfor %}
        </tr>
    {% endfor %}
</tbody>
